broker or maybe with somebody from the city or putting them in touch with resources. Who determines failure to assist? I just think we should maybe try to go beyond maybe what other communities have done here and be a little more concrete. Sorry, I'm saying I think we should go beyond what the other communities ordinances have done here and try to be a little more concrete because

