95
00:41:23,845 --> 00:41:52,702
But kind of in conjunction with the conversation around what our condo review board would look like, I'm kind of interested in the Lexington example of there not being a hard and fast numerical cap, but whether or not a conversion license can be issued is subject to the conditions on the ground when it's sought. I think it's potentially problematic. It's potentially, I don't know how many denials that would actually result in at the end of the day.

