exemption for two and three families where if someone who lives in a building and intends to stay in one of the units, maybe the second, maybe not even intends to stay in one of the units, but essentially since most of the condo conversions are happening by flippers, you know, if one out of every 50 condo conversions is someone who owns a two family and wants to convert,

99
00:43:10,327 --> 00:43:38,238
maybe we should treat that differently than we treat the other 49, which are, you know, flips. And limit conversions per building per year. Does that more apply to the larger buildings where it's like, if you have 40 units, you can only do a certain, okay. Yeah, because, so I think that would have to be, we'd have to have a regime for anything four plus and anything,

